import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib . pyplot as plt

c = np.array([(50,50), (50,100),(150,255),(150,150),(255,255)])
t1 = np.linspace(0, c[0,1], c[0,0]+1).astype('uint8')
t2 = np.linspace(c[0,1] + 1, c[1,1], c[1,0] - c[0,0]).astype('uint8')
t3 = np.linspace(c[1,1] + 1, c[2,1], c[2,0] - c[1,0]).astype('uint8')
t4 = np.linspace(c[2,1] + 1, c[3,1], c[3,0] - c[2,0]).astype('uint8')
t5 = np.linspace(c[3,1] + 1, 255, 255 - c[3,0]).astype('uint8')
transform = np.concatenate((t1, t2), axis=0).astype('uint8')
transform = np.concatenate((transform, t3), axis=0).astype('uint8')
transform = np.concatenate((transform, t4), axis=0).astype('uint8')
transform = np.concatenate((transform, t5), axis=0).astype('uint8')

im_orig = cv.imread('emma_gray.jpeg', cv.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
image_transformed = cv.LUT(im_orig ,transform )

fig,ax = plt.subplots(1,3, figsize=(16,16))

ax[0].plot ( transform )
ax[0].xaxis.tick_top()
ax[0] . set_xlabel( r'Input , $f (\mathbf { x } ) $')
ax[0] . set_ylabel('Output , $\mathrm{T } [ f ( \mathbf { x } ) ]$')
ax[0] . set_xlim(0 ,255)
ax[0] . set_ylim(0 ,255)
ax[0] . set_aspect ('equal')
ax[1].imshow(im_orig, cmap='gray', vmin=0, vmax=255)
ax[1].xaxis.tick_top()
ax[2].imshow(image_transformed, cmap='gray', vmin=0, vmax=255)
ax[2].xaxis.tick_top()
plt.savefig('transform1.jpeg')

plt.show

import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib . pyplot as plt

img = cv.imread('brain.png', cv.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
hist = cv.calcHist([img], [0], None, [256], [0,256])
plt.plot(hist)

plt.xlim([0,256])
plt.show()

(a) White matter accentuate

in here white matter becomes close to white and grey matter is turned as close to black

import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib . pyplot as plt

c = np.array([(100,20), (100,200),(180,255),(180,20),(255,0)])
t1 = np.linspace(0, c[0,1], c[0,0]+1).astype('uint8')
t2 = np.linspace(c[0,1] + 1, c[1,1], c[1,0] - c[0,0]).astype('uint8')
t3 = np.linspace(c[1,1] + 1, c[2,1], c[2,0] - c[1,0]).astype('uint8')
t4 = np.linspace(c[2,1] + 1, c[3,1], c[3,0] - c[2,0]).astype('uint8')
t5 = np.linspace(c[3,1] + 1, 0, 255 - c[3,0]).astype('uint8')
transform = np.concatenate((t1, t2), axis=0).astype('uint8')
transform = np.concatenate((transform, t3), axis=0).astype('uint8')
transform = np.concatenate((transform, t4), axis=0).astype('uint8')
transform = np.concatenate((transform, t5), axis=0).astype('uint8')

im_orig = cv.imread('brain.png', cv.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
image_transformed = cv.LUT(im_orig ,transform )

fig,ax = plt.subplots(1,3, figsize=(16,16))

ax[0].plot ( transform )
ax[0].xaxis.tick_top()
ax[0] . set_xlabel( r'Input , $f (\mathbf { x } ) $')
ax[0] . set_ylabel('Output , $\mathrm{T } [ f ( \mathbf { x } ) ]$')
ax[0] . set_xlim(0 ,255)
ax[0] . set_ylim(0 ,255)
ax[0] . set_aspect ('equal')
ax[1].imshow(im_orig, cmap='gray', vmin=0, vmax=255)
ax[1].xaxis.tick_top()
ax[2].imshow(image_transformed, cmap='gray', vmin=0, vmax=255)

import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

im = cv.imread('gama.jpeg', cv.IMREAD_COLOR)
im = cv.cvtColor(im, cv.COLOR_BGR2LAB)

gamma =1

t1 = np.array([(i/255)**gamma*255 for i in range (0,256)]).astype(np.uint8)
im2 = t1[im[:,:,0]]

fig,ax = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize=(8,16))
ax[0].imshow(im, cmap='gray', vmin=0, vmax=255)
ax[0].xaxis.tick_top()
ax[1].imshow(im2, cmap='gray', vmin=0, vmax=255)
ax[1].xaxis.tick_top()


plt.show

import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

im = cv.imread('gama.jpeg', cv.IMREAD_COLOR)
im = cv.cvtColor(im, cv.COLOR_BGR2LAB)

hist1 = cv.calcHist([im], [0], None, [256], [0,256])
plt.plot(hist1)



gamma = 2

t1 = np.array([(i/255)**gamma*255 for i in range (0,256)]).astype(np.uint8)
im2 = t1[im[:,:,0]]


hist2 = cv.calcHist([im2], [0], None, [256], [0,256])
plt.plot(hist2)

plt.plot(hist1, label=r'Original')
plt.plot(hist2, label = '$\gamma = 2$' )
plt.legend()
